data.text:
The Harley Dome Cologne event was a friendly, professionally organized gathering of around 3,000 Harley-Davidson bikers. It took place at the scenic "Tanzbrunnen" open-air event area and boasted many bands with national and international reputation. Excellent custom bikes were there to be admired - in the exhibition area as well as the ones brought along by the participants. A must-see for all of you next year. The plan is to organize this event for the next consecutive five years.

Arch Number and Arch Name: NM-719

Other arch reference numbers: NABSQNO 12S-749299-4073432

Arch Location (Country/State/County/Canyon): US/NM/San Juan/ Farmington Glade (Chokecherry) Canyon

Arch reported and documented by (with dates): Marsha Rutledge, October 2019

Arch Dimensions: Span 3.5 ft. Height 4 ft.

Type of rock / Type of arch: San Jose Sandstone and Composite / Fin

GPS UTM Coordinates (Zone, Easting / Northing): 12S 749299E / 4073432N

GPS Latitude/Longitude (Decimal Degrees): 36.77391 deg. N / 108.20670 deg. W

Land ownership: BLM GPS Datum: NAD83/WGS84

Additional comments:

Directions: On the west side of Farmington, New Mexico, start at the intersection of NM Highway 170 and Pinion Hills Blvd. Drive east on Pinion Hills Blvd. to mp 2.37 and turn left (north) into Farmington Glade Canyon (aka Chokecherry Canyon) on a dirt road. Restart mileage here and drive .25 mile up Glade Canyon and turn right (east) and drive across the wash and park. Walk a short distance south to the arch, which is in the rocks there.
